                    </div>
                    <span>Read it openly as a Human - not as a Black man or a Catholic woman - simply as a Human.<P>Like it or not it really does take a village to raise a child and we are all children of the same village - Earth.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Postmodern Garbage</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>1</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>1</span>
                      /
                      <span>30</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2004-06-14</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>Christians, beware of this book. Its message is untruth, and blasphemy. We are asked to sacrifice what we hold true for the sake of the world. Take heed, we are not designed for this world, but a better one Where God reigns supreme, and we live eternally in his Holy presence. I gave this book "1 star" because there was effort, and I enjoy a good rebuttle every now and then. <BR>Why is my review entitled "Postmodern Garbage". Simply put, we are in an era of Postmodernism, which is really known as the "whatever feels good", or "its all relative" group. Postmodernists believe there is no truth, but to believe there is no truth means that "its true there is no truth", which is contradictory. Their philosophy is highly uneducated, but extremly tempting. If you look what Christianity has survived you will see by the grace of God postmodern thought will fade away too. What this "educated" author wrote is nothing new. Since the New Testament we've battled postmodern thought, the apostle Paul wrote to Greeks who were trying to mix the old pagan religion with Christianity. Paul tells us in the scripture that there is nothing new under the sun, meaning that every "new thought, new movement(postmodernism)" is not actually new. <BR>Of course, the authors intentions were genuine, but never the less they are still dangerous. <P> We survived the "modernist age"(which is dead I might add), evolution is constantly debunked, communism is a failure.....etc. A certain reviewer asked us to seek the truth in our heart, but I ask you to seek the real Truth, Christ. Do not change for this era. If you still want to read this "pleasant, hopeful, and tear jerking" book, proceed. I only ask that after you read this book, read Dr. Gene Edward Veith's "Postmodern Times: A contemporary......."(its a long title). Take care</span>
                  
              
